# Long COVID Recovery Pattern Tracker

Private, single-user health app. Stack: Next.js App Router + TypeScript,
Tailwind + shadcn/ui, Recharts, Supabase (Postgres + Auth, cloud), Drizzle.
Deploy on Vercel.

Build ONE slice at a time, following `docs/implementation-plan.md`. Do not
scaffold future slices. Write that slice's tests in the same slice.

Non-negotiables:
- The analysis engine in `lib/analysis/` is already built and verified. Do NOT
  rewrite its statistics. `analysis-engine.test.ts` is a frozen acceptance gate
  that must stay green; never weaken a test to make a feature pass.
- No LLM in the inference path. Statistics decide what counts as a pattern; an
  LLM may only structure notes and narrate already-computed results (Slice 4b),
  behind an explicit opt-in.
- Insights are associations, never diagnoses. Use "possible pattern", "watch",
  "collecting data". Never "diagnosis", "causal", or verdicts like
  "improving/declining".
- Never analyse same-day load -> symptom as evidence (reverse causation).
  Lagged effects only.
- Privacy first: row-level security on every table, user-scoped queries, no
  third-party analytics.
- Calm UX, never gamified, never nudge toward more activity. "Insufficient data"
  is a normal, first-class state.
